{"id":"2212.05739","submitter":"Yongtao Li","authors":"Yongtao Li, Lu Lu, Yuejian Peng","title":"Spectral extremal graphs for the bowtie","comments":"21 pages, 5 figures. In the second version, we improved the\n  presentation","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.CO math.SP","license":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","abstract":"  Let $F_k$ be the graph obtained from $k$ triangles by sharing a common\nvertex. The $F_k$-free graphs of order $n$ which attain the maximal spectral\nradius was firstly characterized by Cioab\\u{a}, Feng, Tait and Zhang [Electron.\nJ. Combin. 27 (4) (2020)], and later uniquely determined by Zhai, Liu and Xue\n[Electron. J. Combin. 29 (3) (2022)] under the condition that $n$ is\nsufficiently large. In this paper, we get rid of the condition $n$ being\nsufficiently large if $k=2$. We show that the unique $n$-vertex $F_2$-free\nspectral extremal graph is the balanced complete bipartite graph adding an edge\nin the vertex part with smaller size if $n\\ge 7$, and the condition $n\\ge 7$ is\ntight. Moreover, we show that the unique $m$-edge $F_2$-free spectral extremal\ngraph is the join of $K_2$ with an independent set of $\\frac{m-1}{2}$ vertices\nif $m\\ge 8$, and the condition $m\\ge 8$ is tight.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 12 Dec 2022 07:36:56 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 9 Jan 2023 14:55:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-01-10"}
